  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The main focus of this role is testing the Web applications for key security vulnerabilities, verifying the findings,&#xD;
    and communicating them to the interested stakeholders. In many cases, the security testing is performed by using an&#xD;
    automated testing tool.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <skills>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The person in this role should have these skills:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Good&amp;nbsp;understanding&amp;nbsp;of security testing approaches and techniques&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Good understanding of Web application security&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Experience in debugging and diagnostic skills in the security domain&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Knowledge of the types of systems and applications&amp;nbsp;under test&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Training in the use of security test automated tools&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Experience using the security test automated tools&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></skills>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription>
